# =============================================================================
# WINDOWS RESERVED FILENAMES - ENTERPRISE PROTECTION
# These names are reserved by Windows and cause issues with ZIP/backup tools
# Reference: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/fileio/naming-a-file
# =============================================================================
# Device names (case-insensitive, with or without extension)
[Cc][Oo][Nn]
[Pp][Rr][Nn]
[Aa][Uu][Xx]
[Nn][Uu][Ll]
[Cc][Oo][Mm][0-9]
[Ll][Pp][Tt][0-9]
# Also match in subdirectories
**/[Cc][Oo][Nn]
**/[Pp][Rr][Nn]
**/[Aa][Uu][Xx]
**/[Nn][Uu][Ll]
**/[Cc][Oo][Mm][0-9]
**/[Ll][Pp][Tt][0-9]
# With any extension
**/[Cc][Oo][Nn].*
**/[Pp][Rr][Nn].*
**/[Aa][Uu][Xx].*
**/[Nn][Uu][Ll].*
**/[Cc][Oo][Mm][0-9].*
**/[Ll][Pp][Tt][0-9].*

